<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Baramos: I think the idea that &quot;snare and root would be overpowering for Mages&quot; is a Sacred Cow that needs to be slaughtered, particularly when speaking of PoP soloing.<br>
<br>
Raz: I have made my opinion on this known elsewhere, and when brainstorming I do not wish to discourage ideas. However, I do think that we should be looking for a minimal change that allows us to solo, and I think root and snare would be profound for mages. Perhaps a profound change is needed, but it is not even clear that root or snare will solve the problem.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
We'll have to agree to disagree on whether root and/or snare would be a profound change.  In my view, snare or root is no longer &quot;profound&quot; in the context of other classes, and PoP.  Within the context of the Mage class it is seen as profound only because of the fact that it is a Sacred Cow.  This Sacred Cow effect makes for what I consider fallacious statements, within the current context of PoP, and within the soloing context of the comparative soloing ability of the Mage VS our traditional brethren soloers. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Baramos: Mage pets, even the inflated HP Rathe's Son, disappear so quickly in the face of unslowed MOBs that it truly will make you laugh.<br>
<br>
Raz: This is the problem, but is root or snare the solution?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
It is <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>A</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> solution.  Keep the MOB snared, and aggro on you, and the pet won't be taking a ton of damage.  <br>
<br>
I think there are other possibilities. <br>
<br>
That's why we're brainstorming. The idea is to think outside the box first, come up with as many potential solutions as we can, and then talk to the owners of &quot;tweaked parameters&quot; and find out what we can negotiate, and what the &quot;cost&quot; is.  After feedback, we can continue to craft a solution. Not that Verant's going to listen, but it's nice to talk about such things, from a design and wish perspective.<br>
<br>
I've seen some nice ideas here, other than snare.  I do agree, to a degree, with a poster who said he'd like to see us stay within the parameters of &quot;old style Mage soloing&quot; where the pet acts as damage mitigator while Mage dishes out damage.  Certainly feels right from the perspective of tradition.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Baramos: Give us Snare at level 65, I say.<br>
<br>
Raz: I think we need a solution at 61st level, or 62nd at latest. Do we really want snare and turn into kiters? This would make us more like wizards.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yeah, 61 or 62 is fine, for a solution.  I mention snare at 65 in anticipation of knee-jerk from the Anti-Snare Sacred Cow Committee (ASSCC) at VI, even though this is hypothetical musing.<br>
<br>
As to the comment about snare and kiting, in the context of being given a quick, existing, easily added spell to a Mage arsenal that would allow us to solo, no I wouldn't mind &quot;being more like Wizards&quot;.   We aggro kite as Mages anyway, but without snare it's usually doom.<br>
<br>
On the other hand, as mentioned above, I do like the author's suggestion elsewhere in this to maintain Mage soloing &quot;purity&quot; by staying within the prior conditions of Mage solo activity.  If I were a beta tester, class designer, or had the ear of Verant in some way, it is in solutions (or potential solutions) like those, and not snare/root, for which I would expend the most energy fighting.<br>
<br>
I'm looking forward to more suggestions. =)<br>
<br>
Good thread.<br>
<br>
Bara <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jochangaladar>Jochan Galadar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 887<br> <font color=#333333>(1/29/03 7:39:26 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=456.topic&index=31>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: the HOUR of POWER</span><hr size=1> A few things to say:<br>
<br>
1.  Soloing 61 and 62 in PoP is doable, at least somewhat, in PoJ.  The trick in that case is figuring out how to reliably get singles.<br>
<br>
2.  In my opinion, I would go for having pet damage mitigation increased, or maybe some bigger hit points.<br>
<br>
3.  As tempting as it is, I do NOT want to have snare in my repertoire.  I'm not a druid, ranger, necromancer, wizard, or shadow knight.<br>
<br>
4.  Our pet chaining AA's are a big boon, so duoing is always a possibility, especially in Tier 1 planes.  Even possible in Tier 2. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#333333>- </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower>The Magician's Tower</a><font color=#333333> - </font><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32>Class Balance</a> <font color=#333333> - </font><a href="http://www.magecompendium.com/">The Mage Compendium</a><font color=#333333> - </font>  <br><br><table border=0 align=center><tr><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">Upgrade your account to ezSupporter...</a></td><td><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/image/spacer.gif" width=15 height=1 border=0></td><td align=center><a href="http://login.ezboard.com/BBSSystem.showUserPaymentScreen" target="_blank">...and never see another ad or pop-up again</a></td></tr></table><CENTER><!-- START BOTTOM AD SCRIPT -->
